description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essex Lodge Surgery&lt;/strong&gt; (London E13 0AS) is looking for an experienced part-time (up to 24 hours per week, potential to full-time, subject to review) &lt;strong&gt;Practice Nurse &lt;/strong&gt;to join our friendly team. Experience of working in General Practice (Primary Medical Care) as a Practice Nurse is essential. It’s a challenging role, but nonetheless rewarding, providing healthcare services to the local community. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Essex Lodge Surgery is an expanding PMS and teaching practice serving approximately 12,700 patients in Newham with 2 GP Partners, 5 Salaried GPs, 1 regular locum GPs, 1 GP Registrar, 1 full-time Advanced Nurse Practioner, 1 part-time Nurse Prescriber, 2 Part-time Practice Nurses and 1 HCA, 1 Clinical Pharmacist, and a friendly admin and managerial team. Practice is located in Plaistow, London (E13 0AS) less than 10 minutes’ walk from Plaistow underground station. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic, professional &lt;strong&gt;General Practice Nurse&lt;/strong&gt; who has experience of working within a busy GP surgery &lt;strong&gt;using ‘EMIS WEB’ Clinical System.&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will become part of our busy Nursing team and strive to ensure our patients receive the best possible service from the Practice. You will be contributing to the success of our high QOF achieving practice and overall clinical performance targets with excellent patient scores.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Working hours are up to 24 hours per week (potential to full-time, subject to review). Surgery opening Hours are between Monday 07.30am to 19.00pm, Tuesday to Friday from 08:00am to 18:30pm and Saturday 08:00am to 13:30pm. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The ideal candidate should have excellent clinical, organisational and time management skills. Attention to detail and ability to work in a team are also important, whilst maintaining accuracy and confidentiality.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Application must have current UK professional registration (NMC Registration). &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Essex Lodge Surgery offers&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;• A competitive salary for this role &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;• Fantastic career prospects and opportunities for career development &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;• 4 weeks annual leave plus bank holidays (pro rata)&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;• Training and ongoing development to support their role &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;• NHS Pensions&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For any queries with regards to this job advert, please contact Shima Haque, Practice Manager at &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;shima.haque@nhs.net&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please be informed that all applications &amp; CV’s must be submitted via NHS Jobs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing date for applications &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;13/11/2020.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You are advised to apply as soon as possible. Please note that this vacancy may close before the advertised closing date if sufficient suitable applications are received. If you have not heard from us within 4 weeks of the closing date you should assume you have not been shortlisted but we would like to thank you for your interest at Essex Lodge Surgery&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Additional Information&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note that offers of employment are subject to receipt of satisfactory pre-employment checks.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Essex Lodge Surgery, we actively promote diversity and equal opportunities.&lt;/p&gt;
